    <eposap:WebService>
        <dct:title>Weekly Volcanic Activity Report Metadata</dct:title>
        <dct:description>This web API endpoint will return metadata on weekly volcanic activity report documents produced by the IMO about Icelandic volcanoes in JSON arrays. These metadata contain DCAT-typical information (file type, size, contacts, temporal validity, file download URL, language, etc.) and a geoJSON structure under the spatial parameter to indicate which volcanoes are included in the report. The file download URL is given as value for parameter URI.
        The weekly volcano activity report is a periodic status update about the geophysical activity at one or multiple volcanoes based on qualitative assessment of various observational data of the types remote-sensing, seismic, geodetic, geochemical. The reports summarize any such activity and changes thereof, and may indicate possible unrest or ground effects as opposed to VONA reports which are only aimed at air traffic management.</dct:description>
