        <dct:title>Volcano Observatory Notice for Aviation Metadata</dct:title>
        <dct:description>This web API endpoint will return metadata on VONA (Volcano Observatory Notice for Aviation) documents produced by the IMO about Icelandic volcanoes in JSON arrays. These metadata contain DCAT-typical information (file type, size, contacts, temporal validity, file download URL, language, etc.) and a geoJSON structure under the spatial parameter to indicate which volcano's status is described in the report. The file download URL is given as value for parameter URI.
        Volcano Observatory Notices for Aviation (VONA) are succinct, plain-English messages aimed at dispatchers, pilots, and air-traffic controllers to inform them of volcanic unrest and eruptive activity that could produce ash-cloud hazards.
